name: In the eye of the beholder #2
description: When she is alone her eyes don't close on their own, she clings to them like to a totem, struggling to find a home; and her hands, they tend to glide up and down the length of her length, never far from the bed; and her mind, she is not without it's thoughts, but she avoids them like the plague, and dreams rarely contain more than a vagrant's burden. Hiding in the corner of her bed is a fancied notion, that foxhounette dog that pecks her head often when she passes through the gables; but it is better for her to dwell in the obscurity that is her breast, for if she could feel anything at all it is certain tha t she knows how to die.
